---

# Overview

This lab demonstrates how an application attempts to prevent Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) attacks by validating the `Referer` header instead of using anti-CSRF tokens.

The implementation is flawed because the server only checks whether the expected domain appears somewhere inside the `Referer` header, rather than validating the actual origin of the request. As a result, an attacker can craft a malicious URL that includes the trusted domain as part of the query string and successfully bypass the protection.

